\begin_inset Formula $q^{2}$
\end_inset

 the scale to which the coupling is extrapolated.
 The number 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{f}$
\end_inset

 counts the quark flavors.
 Strong interactions involving a large momentum scale the coupling goes
 to
\begin_inset Formula $\underset{q\rightarrow\infty}{\lim}\alpha_{s}(q^{2})=0$
\end_inset

.
 Quark are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

asymptotically free
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 so that perturbative theory can be applied.
